    <profileDesc>
      <creation>
        The main text of the Torah was created by
        <persName>Simcha ben Chananel</persName>
        between
        <date>25 March and 31 May 1720</date>, see the colophon on folios 342v – 343r. The text of the Haftarah must have been created not much later. In the colophons that close the translation of Exodus, Leviticus, Number and Deuteronomy — see folios 157v
        (line 14), 207v (line 5), 278v (line 2), 342v (line 5), respectively — the copyist states that the text of the Pentateuch he copied is his own translation (<emph>peshat</emph>).
      </creation>
